power\" and US would \"oversee Venezuela\"\n- The event happened on Jan 3, 2026, well before the expiration date\n\nWhile U.S. ground forces did enter Venezuelan territory in combat capacity and achieved the capture of Maduro, the official statements indicate the operation was primarily for capture and extraction (\"joint military and law enforcement raid\") rather than a sustained effort to seize/hold territory, or establish control of a major population center. The evidence weighs toward this being more of a special operations raid focused on capturing an individual leader, rather than removing the sitting government in the broader sense meant by the proposition, despite the language about overseeing Venezuela post-operation.\n\nBased on the specific carve-out in the proposition that \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation: NO\" and the admitted evidence showing this was primarily a short-term capture operation without indication of lasting territorial control or occupation, I'm submitting my vote.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7df9c03eb22c48ce8bffba53","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demon"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demon","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782786507902,"responseId":"gen-1782786508-mndgv8ljcTcj7yUNSfLn"}}
